253
0:32:20,33 --> 0:32:29,48
Large numbers of bait fish help support a
community of predators.


254
0:32:29,48 --> 0:32:35,25
Reserves like this protect wild creatures
from overfishing, but not from a larger cycle


255
0:32:35,25 --> 0:32:43,0
of awakening and dying that defines the Sea
of Cortez.


256
0:32:43,0 --> 0:32:50,5
John Steinbeck and Ed Ricketts sailed into
the cool, rich waters of La Ni–a.


257
0:32:50,5 --> 0:32:59,53
Inevitably, they give way to the warm waters
of El Ni–o.


258
0:32:59,53 --> 0:33:12,39
This climatic shift brings rain to the Baja
Peninsula, along with glimmers of green.


259
0:33:12,39 --> 0:33:18,1
Washing down hillsides and gullies, the rains
deliver a flood of nutrients to shallow lagoons


260
0:33:18,1 --> 0:33:21,94
and mangrove swamps.


261
0:33:21,94 --> 0:33:27,77
Within the protective shelter of mangrove
roots, young yellow snappers and other fish


262
0:33:27,77 --> 0:33:30,22
can now grow and mature.


263
0:33:30,22 --> 0:33:41,9
Out at sea, El Ni–o is a time of scarcity.
The influx of warm water stifles the upwelling


264
0:33:41,9 --> 0:33:51,76
of nutrients. The Sea of Cortez can then grow
fallow, turning clear and lifeless.


265
0:33:51,76 --> 0:33:58,2
That can wreak havoc on some critical habitats,
including dense forests of sargassum, or brown


266
0:33:58,2 --> 0:34:3,44
algae, that grow along the shorelines.


267
0:34:3,44 --> 0:34:12,62
A wide variety of fish use them as a refuge
in their early stages of development. Then,


268
0:34:12,62 --> 0:34:18,25
when wind and waves pull patches of sargassum
from the shore, these fish hitch a ride out


269
0:34:18,25 --> 0:34:22,62
to their ocean habitats.


270
0:34:22,62 --> 0:34:32,129
As sargassum dwindles during El Ni–o, so
do a range of fish populations.


271
0:34:32,129 --> 0:34:38,35
Many ocean creatures are known to travel widely
in pursuit of food supplies that shift with


272
0:34:38,35 --> 0:34:48,1
the seasons or with the climate.


273
0:34:48,1 --> 0:34:55,159
Pacific white-sided dolphins, traveling in
