286
0:36:40,9 --> 0:36:49,94
they stay in flight for days or weeks at a
time, riding wind currents to conserve energy.


287
0:36:49,94 --> 0:36:57,21
Frigates are known to snag flying fish out
of the air, or to steal fish caught by other


288
0:36:57,21 --> 0:37:2,55
birds.


289
0:37:2,55 --> 0:37:12,8
Soaring high above the ocean, they watch for
signs of activity on the surface. If predators


290
0:37:12,8 --> 0:37:19,6
force small fish to the surface, frigates
